<h1>Accessibility</h1>
<p>Like localization, accessibility is an important aspect of Firefox copy creation. Similarly, writing well for the web – short sentences, clear hierarchy, non-ambiguous language – supports accessibility efforts. Additional considerations include the use of descriptive and meaningful alt text. <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG20/glance/"Learn more about accessible design</a> 
<p>It is also important to be fair and respectful when we talk about all Firefox users, regardless of how they use our products to access the Web. <a href="https://adata.org/factsheet/ADANN-writing"Read about removing bias in accessibility language</a> 
